The track, a cover of The Waterboys song, is for the new Richard Curtis film About Time.The video features a montage of clips from Curtis's well-known rom-coms Love Actually, Notting Hill and Four Weddings and a Funeral.It also shows clips from the upcoming film.The movie features Domhnall Gleeson who discovers his father, played by Bill Nighy, can time travel. He decides to make his world a better place by getting a girlfriend (Rachel McAdams).The full soundtrack to the film, which also includes a reworking of Ben Folds' 'The Luckiest', is set to be released September 2.
